th and east asian trade", "year": 2008, "source": "social science research network", "authors": [{"name": "shiro armstrong", "affiliation": "australian national university"}, {"name": "peter drysdale", "affiliation": "australian national university"}, {"name": "kaliappa kalirajan", "affiliation": "australian national university"}], "id": 2751751161}, {"title": "asian trade structures and trade potential an initial analysis of south and east asian trade", "year": 2008, "source": "research papers in economics", "authors": [{"name": "shiro armstrong", "affiliation": "australian national university"}, {"name": "peter drysdale"}, {"name": "kaliappa kalirajan"}], "id": 3121261024}, {"title": "regional cooperation in east asia and fta strategies", "year": 2005, "source": "research papers in economics", "authors": [{"name": "peter drysdale"}], "id": 3121261024}, {"title": "regional cooperation in east asia and fta strategies", "year": 2005, "source": "", "authors": [{"name": "peter drysdale"}]}, {"title": "regional cooperation in east asia and fta strategies", "year": 2006, "source": "", "authors": [{"name": "peter drysdale"}]}], "ANDS-Grants": [{"description": "Chinese Outward Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) has grown rapidly, making it a significant contributor to global economic development and Australia's economic growth, and its importance can only be expected to grow. As well as bringing substantial benefits to recipient countries, the experience of Chinese firms investing abroad are most likely to have a bearing on the continued liberalisation of China's economic institutions. The project aims to identify the causes and drivers of Chinese FDI, which will give a better understanding of how Chinese FDI can be expected to evolve over the coming decade and how Australian regulation of FDI might best capture the benefits it offers.", "title": "Linkage Projects - Grant ID: LP130101094", "id": "516849", "institutions": ["Australian National University"], "key": "http://purl